      "writtenOn": "2021-10-09T04:50:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "i have two concerns\n\n(minor) these files weren\u0027t meant to be read by humans, and i\u0027m not sure there\u0027s value in beautifying the output.  if we were to pregen the files for all the arches we care about and commit the files to the tree, the resulting file will larger and have more lines changing leading to more noise.  i\u0027m not sure seeing the diff on a per-insn level would ever be useful to humans ?  personally i\u0027ve only found value in seeing the source generation policy/logic ...\n\n(not minor) is the endianness correct ?  we (and prob most people) are going to emit little endian because the python tool is executing in the SDK which is x86_64.\n\nseems like just emitting the raw buffer as-is and setting the alignment to 32-bit would be easier.",
      "parentUuid": "aed9ae71_3794f262",
      "revId": "47d1592896ab56df7b71d13f3b7f3499165c9d17",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889"
    },
