        "id": 1572669
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-10-11T17:42:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The endianness concern is a good point, although I think the compiler also just uses struct.pack(), so it already won\u0027t be correct if the build and host systems have different endianness: https://android.googlesource.com/platform/external/minijail/+/HEAD/tools/bpf.py#156 (Is there an actual BPF spec somewhere? I couldn\u0027t find a definitive source for the expected endianness, but it seems like it is the host endianness in the case of the Linux kernel implementation.)\n\nI am OK with just setting the alignment to 4 bytes instead.  The human-readable formatting was mostly a fun distraction once I started to look into how to split the fields back out.",
      "parentUuid": "7c24f224_d86af2db",
      "revId": "47d1592896ab56df7b71d13f3b7f3499165c9d17",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889"
    },
